---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Evaluator">
  <h1>Evaluator</h1>

  <p>Runs an agent against test cases and scores quality using both schema validation and LLM judgment.</p>

  <h2>Interface</h2>
  <pre><code>import &lcub; Evaluator &rcub; from "agent-forge/evaluator";
import &lcub; createOllamaBackend &rcub; from "agent-forge/llm_backend/ollama";

const llm = createOllamaBackend();
const evaluator = new Evaluator(llm);

const report = await evaluator.run(&lcub;
  agentCode: agentCodeString,
  testCases: [
    &lcub;
      id: "tc-1",
      input: &lcub; pr_url: "https://github.com/org/repo/pull/1", repo: "org/repo" &rcub;,
      expectedSchema: &lcub; keys: ["issues", "score", "summary"] &rcub;,
      tracedTo: ["logic errors"],
      diversityScore: 1,
    &rcub;,
  ],
  description: "review PRs for logic errors",
  outputSchema: &lcub; issues: "array", score: "number", summary: "string" &rcub;,
&rcub;);

// report.testPassRate: 0.0 - 1.0
// report.judgeScore: 0.0 - 1.0
// report.composite: 0.6 * testPassRate + 0.4 * judgeScore
// report.passed: boolean</code></pre>

  <h2>ScoreReport Fields</h2>
  <pre><code>interface ScoreReport &lcub;
  testPassRate: number;
  judgeScore: number;
  composite: number;
  generalizationScore?: number;
  generalizationWarning?: string;
  coverageGaps: string[];
  testResults: TestResult[];
  passed: boolean;
&rcub;

interface TestResult &lcub;
  testCase: TestCase;
  passed: boolean;
  output?: unknown;
  error?: string;
  executionTimeMs: number;
&rcub;</code></pre>

  <h2>Execution</h2>
  <p>Each test case is executed via <code>bun:eval</code> in an isolated subprocess:</p>
  <pre><code>// Temporary files created per test
const agentFile = "`/tmp/agent-forge-evals/agent_` + runId + `.ts`";
const runtimeFile = "`/tmp/agent-forge-evals/runtime_` + runId + `.ts`";
const inputFile = "`/tmp/agent-forge-evals/input_` + runId + `.json`";

// Files cleaned up after execution
bun run agent_" + runId + ".ts</code></pre>

  <h2>LLM Judge</h2>
  <p>The judge evaluates up to 3 test outputs (sampled) for semantic quality:</p>
  <pre><code>// Judge prompt instructs LLM to score 0-25 per criterion:
// - Correctness
// - Completeness
// - Quality
// - Format Compliance

// judgeScore = average(criterion_scores) / 25</code></pre>

  <h2>Generalization Shadow Eval</h2>
  <p>After main tests, 3 shadow cases run to check generalization. These are synthetic inputs that are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Within the intended scope</li>
    <li>Not similar to training inputs</li>
  </ul>
  <p>A warning is attached if the agent fails 2/3 or more shadow cases.</p>

  <h2>Customization</h2>
  <p>Key constants in <code>src/evaluator.ts</code>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>AGENT_RUNTIME_PACKAGE</code> — the runtime shim injected for all agent executions</li>
    <li><code>MAX_SHADOW_CASES</code> — number of generalization holdout tests (default: 3)</li>
    <li><code>EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS</code> — per-test execution timeout (default: 30000ms)</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
